1
00:00:00,520 --> 00:00:06,040
If I had to guess one of your biggest struggles
in trading, it would be not knowing when to

2
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:10,570
take your profit, or let the trade run to
its full potential.

3
00:00:10,570 --> 00:00:16,330
You often exit a profitable trade with a small
amount, missing a huge opportunity.

4
00:00:16,330 --> 00:00:21,720
And other times you leave the trade open,
just to see the price come back to your entry

5
00:00:21,720 --> 00:00:22,779
level.

6
00:00:22,779 --> 00:00:26,090
What if I told you I have a solution for this?

7
00:00:26,090 --> 00:00:30,830
It involves using Bollinger Bands indicator,
and it will help you finding the trend in

8
00:00:30,830 --> 00:00:35,640
a second and you’ll know exactly where to
set your targets and stop orders.

9
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:41,770
You know the drill, like, subscribe and stick
around for the full video.

10
00:00:41,770 --> 00:00:45,540
Let’s start with the setup of your chart.

11
00:00:45,540 --> 00:00:47,390
This may look weird at first.

12
00:00:47,390 --> 00:00:52,620
We’ll use not one, not 2, but 3 Bollinger
Bands.

13
00:00:52,620 --> 00:00:58,649
First Bollinger Band indicator will have a
period of 200 and a standard deviation of

14
00:00:58,649 --> 00:01:01,219
1.

15
00:01:01,219 --> 00:01:07,320
Second one will have a period of 200 and a
standard deviation of 2.

16
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:14,840
And the third one, the same 200 period and
a standard deviation of 3.

17
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:21,210
And make the middle Bollinger Band more obvious,
increase its thickness and also change its

18
00:01:21,210 --> 00:01:22,659
color.

19
00:01:22,659 --> 00:01:28,430
Now, the main advantage of this system is
the fact that Bollinger Bands which use standard

20
00:01:28,430 --> 00:01:35,390
deviation to establish where hidden support
and resistance levels might be found.

21
00:01:35,390 --> 00:01:38,330
These are also known as volatility channels.

22
00:01:38,330 --> 00:01:45,140
A volatility channel plots lines above and
below a central measure of price.

23
00:01:45,140 --> 00:01:53,219
These lines widen or contract depending on
how volatile or non-volatile a market is.

24
00:01:53,219 --> 00:01:59,320
With this setup you’ll read the trend strength,
you’ll time your entries during trends and

25
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:05,890
during range markets and you’ll also finding
potential reversal points in a dynamic, adaptive

26
00:02:05,890 --> 00:02:06,890
manner.

27
00:02:06,890 --> 00:02:07,890
Determining the trend

28
00:02:07,890 --> 00:02:14,220
I don’t know about you, but for me, with
this setup, the trend is pretty obvious.

29
00:02:14,220 --> 00:02:19,470
In this example, I see an uptrend, but with
different phases.

30
00:02:19,470 --> 00:02:27,190
When price is located between the middle line,
and the first band, we have a weak uptrend.

31
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:32,940
When the price gets within this area, there
is no strong momentum, and the price is likely

32
00:02:32,940 --> 00:02:38,739
to fluctuate within a range, and may even
go below the middle line.

33
00:02:38,739 --> 00:02:45,099
You can enter a buy trade in this area, but
only if you have confluence with other factors.

34
00:02:45,099 --> 00:02:48,599
We’ll talk about this later.

35
00:02:48,599 --> 00:02:54,670
When price is located between the first band
and the second Bollinger band, we have a strong

36
00:02:54,670 --> 00:02:56,680
uptrend.

37
00:02:56,680 --> 00:03:01,040
There is a higher chance that the price will
continue upward.

38
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:06,750
As long as the candles continue to close in
this buy zone, the odds favour maintaining

39
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:12,199
current long positions or even opening new
ones.

40
00:03:12,199 --> 00:03:18,159
When price is located between the second band
and the third Bollinger band above the middle

41
00:03:18,159 --> 00:03:22,180
line, we have a very strong uptrend.

42
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:29,099
Price is overextended and I would avoid buying
if price goes outside the bands.

43
00:03:29,099 --> 00:03:34,819
In this area, if you are experienced, you
could look for divergences, to find reversals

44
00:03:34,819 --> 00:03:35,819
signals.

45
00:03:35,819 --> 00:03:38,790
Again, we’ll talk about this later.

46
00:03:38,790 --> 00:03:42,379
And here’s a downtrend.

47
00:03:42,379 --> 00:03:48,400
Price is below the middle line, between the
200 EMA, and the first band.

48
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,680
This is a weak downtrend.

49
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:57,939
There is no strong momentum, yet, and the
price is likely to fluctuate within a range.

50
00:03:57,939 --> 00:04:04,480
When price is located between the first band
and the second Bollinger band, below the 200

51
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:07,989
EMA, we have a strong downtrend.

52
00:04:07,989 --> 00:04:13,530
There is a higher chance that the price will
continue downward.

53
00:04:13,530 --> 00:04:19,600
When price is located between the second band
and the third Bollinger band, we have a very

54
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:22,320
strong downtrend.

55
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:27,810
You see how this set of 3 bands will give
a better insight into a trend.

56
00:04:27,810 --> 00:04:30,850
You don’t just say, it’s a downtrend.

57
00:04:30,850 --> 00:04:35,740
You evaluate the volatility and the price
location and you know the strength of the

58
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:37,820
trend, which is more powerful.

59
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:39,270
Confluence entries

60
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:42,389
Now you know the strength of a trend.

61
00:04:42,389 --> 00:04:44,950
How and when do you enter?

62
00:04:44,950 --> 00:04:47,960
As always, I rely on confluence.

63
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:55,479
The term confluence refers to the overlap
of two or more key levels or areas of value.

64
00:04:55,479 --> 00:05:00,290
These can be trend lines, horizontal levels,
and even other channels.

65
00:05:00,290 --> 00:05:04,630
Let’s use simple support and resistance
levels.

66
00:05:04,630 --> 00:05:11,290
Looking for overlaps of key levels with Bollinger
Band is an excellent way to find high probability

67
00:05:11,290 --> 00:05:12,449
setups.

68
00:05:12,449 --> 00:05:18,840
These areas of confluence tend to attract
more buyers or sellers, resulting in a reversal

69
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:22,069
or a continuation of the current trend.

70
00:05:22,069 --> 00:05:29,139
With this confluence you are basically finding
pullbacks in a strong trend.

71
00:05:29,139 --> 00:05:34,590
When a market is in an uptrend, meaning price
is above the middle Bollinger band, and you

72
00:05:34,590 --> 00:05:40,590
find a confluence between a recent support
or resistance level and one of the standard

73
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:46,600
deviation bands, you can trade a bounce of
that area.

74
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:53,310
On the other hand, when price is in a downtrend,
below the middle band, and a recent support

75
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:59,990
or resistance aligns with one of the lower
volatility bands, a decent pullback trade

76
00:05:59,990 --> 00:06:02,370
may be on the cards.

77
00:06:02,370 --> 00:06:06,020
Here’s EURJPY.

78
00:06:06,020 --> 00:06:11,900
Before finding the confluence trade, just
look how price was respecting the bands, almost

79
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:13,889
religiously.

80
00:06:13,889 --> 00:06:20,320
Even when price was below the middle band,
it found support at the lower bands.

81
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:24,460
This alone makes this system a very powerful
one.

82
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:25,960
Now look here.

83
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:31,420
Price broke above the middle band and also
broke this resistance level.

84
00:06:31,420 --> 00:06:33,970
Which now will potentially act as a support.

85
00:06:33,970 --> 00:06:36,720
Here’s our value area.

86
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:42,720
The first band above the middle line and this
level are aligning on the same point.

87
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:50,699
So a buy trade, in the strong trend area,
is a decent trend continuation opportunity.

88
00:06:50,699 --> 00:06:54,350
And look how easy is to find profit targets.

89
00:06:54,350 --> 00:06:56,759
You just aim for the next bands.

90
00:06:56,759 --> 00:07:00,430
The first take profit is at the second band.

91
00:07:00,430 --> 00:07:03,520
And the next target is the last band.

92
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:10,340
Always expect a momentum loss when price reaches
the next set of bands.

93
00:07:10,340 --> 00:07:15,250
Always take a part of your profit at these
levels, so you don’t give it back to the

94
00:07:15,250 --> 00:07:21,710
market if price finds resistance and reverses.

95
00:07:21,710 --> 00:07:28,740
In this chart, price broke below the middle
band, enter a weak trend phase, and then also

96
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:31,410
broke this support level.

97
00:07:31,410 --> 00:07:39,370
Then it targeted the second band, retraced,
found resistance once again at the first band,

98
00:07:39,370 --> 00:07:41,169
and then went for the third band.

99
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:45,060
Look how powerful this setup is.

100
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:48,590
Price stopped right at the third band.

101
00:07:48,590 --> 00:07:50,410
Then it retraced back up.

102
00:07:50,410 --> 00:07:53,120
Here’s our value area.

103
00:07:53,120 --> 00:08:00,159
The first band below the middle line and this
previous breakout level are aligning on the

104
00:08:00,159 --> 00:08:02,500
same area.

105
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:07,600
So there’s a potential sell trade, in the
strong trend area.

106
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:13,340
You can enter right after the price touches
the band, or you can wait for a rejection

107
00:08:13,340 --> 00:08:17,270
signal, maybe an engulfing candle or a pin
bar.

108
00:08:17,270 --> 00:08:18,759
It’s up to you.

109
00:08:18,759 --> 00:08:21,810
And you just aim for the next bands.

110
00:08:21,810 --> 00:08:26,940
The first take profit is at the second band
below the middle line.

111
00:08:26,940 --> 00:08:30,190
And the next target is the last band.

112
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:38,169
So I said previously that you can also take
a trade in the weak buy or sell area.

113
00:08:38,169 --> 00:08:41,649
You can do this, if you can find a confluence.

114
00:08:41,649 --> 00:08:46,260
And this may even offer you a higher risk
to reward ratio.

115
00:08:46,260 --> 00:08:47,850
Look right here.

116
00:08:47,850 --> 00:08:53,510
We had a transition for a strong uptrend to
a downtrend.

117
00:08:53,510 --> 00:09:00,070
Price patiently found support at each of the
previous band, and now is returning to the

118
00:09:00,070 --> 00:09:01,250
middle line.

119
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:04,870
But this area is an important one.

120
00:09:04,870 --> 00:09:11,230
I see a supply zone right here, which aligns
with the middle line.

121
00:09:11,230 --> 00:09:16,410
Yes, you can incorporate this setup into supply
and demand trading.

122
00:09:16,410 --> 00:09:19,820
Let me know if you want a future video about
this.

123
00:09:19,820 --> 00:09:25,610
If you are a classic support and resistance
trader, you have this breakout zone here,

124
00:09:25,610 --> 00:09:30,339
a former support, know potentially acting
as resistance.

125
00:09:30,339 --> 00:09:36,589
So, a sell trade in this area is worth risking.

126
00:09:36,589 --> 00:09:41,050
First band below the middle line is the first
take profit area.

127
00:09:41,050 --> 00:09:44,210
The second band is next area.

128
00:09:44,210 --> 00:09:45,779
And finally the third band.

129
00:09:45,779 --> 00:09:51,660
And please, don’t wait until the third band
is reached to exit.

130
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:56,089
Take partial profits at each band, and be
conservative.

131
00:09:56,089 --> 00:09:58,029
Heikin ashi

132
00:09:58,029 --> 00:10:03,810
Heikin ashi candles work very well in combination
with this setup and will make your trading

133
00:10:03,810 --> 00:10:05,850
a lot easier.

134
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:11,360
Heikin Ashi shows the average price movements,
creating a smoother appearance, which helps

135
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:15,050
to identify market momentum more easily.

136
00:10:15,050 --> 00:10:21,500
You have the trend with the help of Bollinger
Bands, and know you add the momentum aspect,

137
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:23,880
using Heikin Ashi candles.

138
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:29,620
If you don’t like candlesticks that may
flip-flop constantly from a green bar to a

139
00:10:29,620 --> 00:10:36,490
red bar to a green bar, maybe you should try
Heikin Ashi charts, because they tend to have

140
00:10:36,490 --> 00:10:41,399
longer stretches of green and red bars.

141
00:10:41,399 --> 00:10:46,480
When the market is above the middle Bollinger
line, look for Heikin-Ashi candlesticks that

142
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:54,370
have big bodies and long upper shadows, but
no lower shadow.

143
00:10:54,370 --> 00:10:59,110
When the market is below the middle Bollinger
line, look for Heikin-Ashi candlesticks that

144
00:10:59,110 --> 00:11:07,880
have big bodies and long lower shadows, but
no upper shadow.

145
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:13,550
What I like about them is the fact that small
corrections and consolidations are somewhat

146
00:11:13,550 --> 00:11:19,209
left behind and they are barely visible on
the chart.

147
00:11:19,209 --> 00:11:25,339
You will also notice that when the direction
changes on a Heikin-Ashi, the price will most

148
00:11:25,339 --> 00:11:28,860
likely go to the next set of bands.

149
00:11:28,860 --> 00:11:35,889
Also, the market noise is filtered, so maybe
there’s a less chance you’ll be distracted

150
00:11:35,889 --> 00:11:38,730
from choppy price action.

151
00:11:38,730 --> 00:11:44,410
And again, you look for support and resistance
levels and important swing points, to find

152
00:11:44,410 --> 00:11:46,170
confluence levels.

153
00:11:46,170 --> 00:11:48,220
Divergence trading

154
00:11:48,220 --> 00:11:54,110
If you want to catch reversals, you could
trade divergences, after price spends a lot

155
00:11:54,110 --> 00:12:00,910
of time in the very strong trend territory,
between the second and the third band of the

156
00:12:00,910 --> 00:12:02,139
setup.

157
00:12:02,139 --> 00:12:08,769
A divergence is an event that is associated
with increased levels of volatility.

158
00:12:08,769 --> 00:12:15,600
I’ve added the MACD histogram, to easily
spot points of inconsistency between price

159
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,170
and indicator.

160
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:23,889
A bearish divergence is when the market makes
a higher high, but the MACD shows a lower

161
00:12:23,889 --> 00:12:27,490
high (which is a sign of weakness).

162
00:12:27,490 --> 00:12:35,029
A bullish divergence is when the market makes
a lower low, but the oscillator shows a higher

163
00:12:35,029 --> 00:12:38,810
low (and this is a sign of strength).

164
00:12:38,810 --> 00:12:44,390
You want the signal to appear when price is
near the outer limits of the bands.

165
00:12:44,390 --> 00:12:47,279
And here’s the trick.

166
00:12:47,279 --> 00:12:51,970
When you find a divergence, you don’t enter
at the third band.

167
00:12:51,970 --> 00:12:54,960
You enter at the second one.

168
00:12:54,960 --> 00:13:00,630
This is a riskier trade, against the trend,
and you know that price likes to rest at the

169
00:13:00,630 --> 00:13:04,760
Bollinger bands, before continuing its move.

170
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:11,190
So you wait for a movement at the second band,
then you target the first band, and the middle

171
00:13:11,190 --> 00:13:14,010
band as the final target.

172
00:13:14,010 --> 00:13:20,280
But most of the times, you’ll have a decent
win rate if you just target the second band.

173
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:22,340
Here’s Bitcoin.

174
00:13:22,340 --> 00:13:30,820
We see a price move outside the bands, while
the MACD indicated a bearish divergence.

175
00:13:30,820 --> 00:13:37,760
This suggests weakness and a potential reversal
to at least the first band, and maybe even

176
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:40,660
the middle Bollinger Band.

177
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:47,160
Very important: always wait for a trendline
breakout before entering into a divergence

178
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,740
trade.

179
00:13:48,740 --> 00:13:53,020
This will filter a lot of fake divergences.

180
00:13:53,020 --> 00:13:59,690
You want to enter after a trendline breakout,
somewhere around the second Bollinger band,

181
00:13:59,690 --> 00:14:02,790
with a stop loss above the third band.

182
00:14:02,790 --> 00:14:09,899
Again: this is a riskier trade, so if it’s
not your style, stick to trend continuation

183
00:14:09,899 --> 00:14:57,529
setups.

184
00:14:57,529 --> 00:15:50,000
Now, if you want to learn more about finding
the best confluence signals, make sure you

185
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,089
watch this video here.

186
00:15:52,089 --> 00:15:55,750
It contains many tips and tricks, you could
add to your arsenal.

187
00:15:55,750 --> 00:16:01,120
And check out our academy program, if you
want to further level up your trading.

188
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:01,980
Until next time!

